---
description: React + Tailwind code conventions
globs: "**/*.tsx"
alwaysApply: false
---

# React
- Functional components + hooks only; keep components small, extract reusable logic into custom hooks.
- Derive state instead of duplicating it across components.
- All API payloads fully typed (no `any`); keep DTOs in dedicated modules.

# Tailwind
- Style via `className` utility classes; no inline styles.
- Use `clsx` (or equivalent) for conditional class lists.
- Prefer low-saturation colors (`slate`, `stone`, `gray`); avoid vivid tones unless needed for clear affordance.

# Accessibility
- Interactive elements must have accessible labels (`aria-label`, `role`, or visible text).
- Handle loading and error states explicitly for all async operations.

# Security
- Never render untrusted HTML; avoid `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.
- Prefer `httpOnly` cookies for auth tokens; do not store secrets in localStorage/sessionStorage.
